title: Pumice Stone
description: A piece of pumice stone, characterized by its light weight and porous texture. The surface is rough with numerous small holes, indicating its volcanic origin.

title: Rock Sample
description: A rough, irregularly shaped rock with a light-colored base and some darker mineral inclusions. The surface appears somewhat shiny and textured, indicating a natural formation.

title: Rock Formation
description: A rough, irregularly shaped rock with a jagged top and a textured surface, showcasing a mix of light and dark colors.

title: Rock Sample
description: A rough, irregularly shaped rock with a light brown base and dark speckles. The surface appears coarse and contains various mineral fragments, suggesting it may be a type of sedimentary rock.

title: Obsidian Rock
description: A piece of obsidian, a naturally occurring volcanic glass, characterized by its smooth, shiny surface and dark color. The rock has a jagged edge and a glossy appearance, typical of obsidian.

title: Mineral Sample
description: A rough, irregularly shaped rock with a dark, shiny surface and some lighter brownish areas. The texture appears coarse, indicating it may be a type of mineral or ore.

title: Black Rock
description: A piece of black rock with a rough texture and visible mineral grains. The rock appears to have a flat surface on one side and a more irregular shape on the other.
